node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Anxiety Healer on August 15, 2021 tagging @anxietyhealer, and @regen_health. May be an image of text that says 'honeybee @punkmom_ Just a friendly reminder that anxiety attacks aren't always hyperventilating rocking back and forth. They are also random bursts of irritability ·obsessive behavior and nit picking hypersensitivity .pacing .silence .zoning out Always look for signs with your loved ones 12/9/17, 2:41 PM'.

node.text:
Mental illness, depression, and anxiety look different on everyone. Check on your people's regards of how “put together” they may seem. Remember that even if people don’t seem to be in distress on the outside, believe them, if they say they are.
Repost via @regen_health
📷 Credits punkmom_ on twitter
